places.title: Notre-Dame Cathedral
places.description: A famous Gothic cathedral located on the Île de la Cité in Paris, known for its stunning architecture.

places.title: Central Park
places.description: A large public park in New York City, offering green spaces, lakes, and walking paths in the heart of Manhattan.

places.title: Eiffel Tower
places.description: An iconic iron structure in Paris, France, recognized worldwide as a symbol of France.

places.title: Big Ben
places.description: The nickname for the Great Bell of the clock at the north end of the Palace of Westminster in London.

places.title: Sagrada Familia
places.description: A large, unfinished basilica in Barcelona, Spain, designed by the architect Antoni Gaudí.
